  "prompt": "Where can I get a custom one-off plastic part manufactured?",
  "response": "There are several options for manufacturing a custom plastic part:\n\n1. Local Machine Shops\n- Can do small-scale custom plastic fabrication\n- Good for prototyping and small runs\n\n2. Online Manufacturing Services\n- Protolabs\n- SendCutSend\n- 3D Hubs\n- Xometry\n- These platforms connect you with manufacturing facilities\n\n3. 3D Printing Services\n- Shapeways\n- Sculpteo\n- i.Materialise\n- Good for complex geometries and small quantities\n\n4. CNC Machining Services\n- Can create precision plastic parts\n- Good for functional prototypes\n\n5. Injection Molding Services\n- Best for larger quantities\n- Companies like RapidMade or MoldingUSA\n\n6. Local Plastics Manufacturers\n- Check regional industrial directories\n- May offer custom fabrication services\n\nFactors to consider:\n- Quantity needed\n- Part complexity\n- Material requirements\n- Budget\n- Turnaround time\n\nI recommend getting quotes from multiple providers and providing detailed specifications for your part.\n\nWould you like help determining the best manufacturing method for your specific part?",
